The border guards told about the situation at the checkpoints in the area of the CAB

02 Nov 2019, 09:58

As of 07.00, all checkpoints at the demarcation line in the area of the Joint Forces operation have been opened according to the autumn schedule and are operating under the established “yellow” mode. The press service of the State Border Guard Service of Ukraine reports.
This morning, there were a number of vehicles in the CPVV for entry and exit.
Mayorske - 20/50; Marinka - 0/70; Novotroitskoye - 20/40; Bending - 20/20.
Over the past 24 hours, over 39.2 thousand people and 5 thousand vehicles have been following through the KPVV:

Mayorske - 8800 people and 1080 vehicles;
Marinka - 8360 people and 1430 vehicles;
"Novotroitske" - 8250 people and 1660 vehicles;
Bending - 3700 people and 850 vehicles;
The village of Lugansk - 10,000 people.

In Novotroitskoye, the border guards of Donetsk detachment stopped the attempt of illegal movement through the line of demarcation of goods in the amount of over 200 thousand hryvnias. Transmitted to DFS representatives.

